Question 2.Question: A cinema hall contains a certain number of people. If 22 ½% are children, 47 ½% are men and 84 are women, find the number of men in the hall.
Question 2.Explanation:
Let the number of people in the cinema be n

Children = 22 ½ % of n

Men = 47½ of n

Total i.e. 70% of n = men & children

Remainder of 30% of n = Women (84)

Thus, Men = 47 ½ % of n

Women = 84 = 30% of n

Let 47½% = m

30% = 84

m = (84 x 47½)/30

= 133 men
